&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A 11 hour per week Band 7 specialist ultrasonographer post has become available at Leeds Fertility which is based at Seacroft Hospital. This is one of the largest reproductive medicine units in the UK and the multidisciplinary team is committed to promoting high standards of care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will work closely with the nursing and clinical team, offering specialist ultrasonography services at all stages of fertility investigation, treatment and early pregnancy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Vicki Rawnsley, Lead nurse on 0113 2063107, email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;v.rawnsley@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;or Nichola Sugden, Advanced Nurse Practitioner on 0113 2063178, email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;nichola.sugden@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
